Recipe for Lemon Garlic Pasta

Ingredients

200 g pasta (spaghetti or penne)
2 tbsp olive oil
2 cloves garlic, minced
Zest and juice of 1 lemon
Salt & black pepper
Optional: grated Parmesan, chopped parsley

Instructions

Cook pasta in salted water according to package instructions; reserve a little pasta water.
Heat olive oil in a pan, sauté garlic gently for 30–60 seconds (don’t brown).
Add lemon zest and juice, then toss in drained pasta.
Add a splash of pasta water if needed, season with salt and pepper.
Serve with Parmesan and parsley if desired.
